<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 05 at 3:31PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Craig
and northwestern Ottawa Counties through 400 PM CDT...
At 331 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Welch, moving northeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Miami...                          Baxter Springs...
Commerce...                       Quapaw...
Welch...                          Treece...
Picher...                         Cardin...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
